cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CG

The paper deals with lower bounds on space complexity for refuting random 3-CNFs in Resolution and algebraic systems. This falls under the area of proof complexity, which is typically categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also uses graph theory techniques, which could potentially place it under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper's focus on matchings and expansions could also place it under cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
